#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:56
msgid ""
"As seen in the previous sections, polygons are central to Blender. Most "
"objects are represented by polygons and truly curved objects are often "
"approximated by polygon meshes. When rendering images, you may notice "
"that these polygons appear as a series of small, flat faces. Sometimes "
"this is a desirable effect, but usually we want our objects to look nice "
"and smooth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:66
msgid "Smooth"
msgstr "Suavizar"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:71
msgid "Shading buttons in Tool Shelf."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:73
msgid ""
"The easiest way is to set an entire object as smooth or faceted by "
"selecting a mesh object, and in *Object Mode*, click *Smooth* in the "
"*Tool Shelf*. This button does not stay pressed; it forces the assignment"
" of the \"smoothing\" attribute to each face in the mesh, including when "
"you add or delete geometry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:79
msgid ""
"Notice that the outline of the object is still strongly faceted. "
"Activating the smoothing features does not actually modify the object's "
"geometry; it changes the way the shading is calculated across the "
"surfaces (normals will be interpolated), giving the illusion of a smooth "
"surface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:84
msgid ""
"Click the *Flat* button in the *Tool Shelf*\\ 's *Shading panel* to "
"revert the shading back (normals will be constant) to that shown in the "
"first image above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:90
msgid "Smoothing Parts of a Mesh"
msgstr "Suavizando partes de uma malha"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:92
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can choose which edges to smooth by entering *Edit "
"Mode*, then selecting some faces and clicking the *Smooth* button. The "
"selected edges are marked in yellow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:96
msgid ""
"When the mesh is in *Edit Mode*, only the selected edges will receive the"
" \"smoothing\" attribute. You can set edges as flat (removing the "
"\"smoothing\" attribute) in the same way by selecting edges and clicking "
"the *Flat* button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:103
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Auto Smooth <auto-smooth>` filter is an quick and easy way to "
"combine smooth and faceted faces in the same object."
msgstr ""

